          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "GetPreviousYearEnergyUsage",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate and return the energy usage for a specified entity from the previous year. Scalar functions return a single value, which can be used in queries to provide specific calculations or transformations based on input parameters."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
